Description: Two joining fragments of neck and flattened handle to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Mousaios. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0830.44.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (191)
